View Document

 

The Document landing page presents the content of the document, aggregated information about specific Document details and properties, related objects and static text. The Document landing page is divided into tabs that contain specific information.

     

    Document header

    Document header contains following information:

    1. Classification - the classification of the document - Condition Report, Treatment Report - Single Object, etc.
    2. Purpose of the document
    3. Single/Multiple - if the document is for single object or for multiple objects
    4. State - current document state
    5. Title of the document

    Reports

    In case you are reviewing a report (Condition Report, Examination Report etc.) the first tab contains the content of the document - created or uploaded in ConservatinonSpace.
